# CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS:
# 1. All URLs must NOT use localhost, 127.0.0.1, 0.0.0.0, .local, or host.docker.internal
# 2. NEXT_PUBLIC_USE_DEV_AUTH must be set to "false"
# 3. JWT_SECRET must be at least 32 characters long
# 4. All required secrets must be set
#
# Required variables:
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_URL (production URL, not localhost)
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_URL (production URL, not localhost)
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_STORAGE_URL (production URL, not localhost)
# - HASURA_ADMIN_SECRET (minimum 32 characters)
# - JWT_SECRET (minimum 32 characters)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI FEATURES (OPTIONAL)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# OpenAI API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Recommended for: Message summarization + semantic search
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...  # For client-side AI features

# Alternative AI Provider Configuration
# Get your API key from your AI provider's console
# Note: Some providers may not support embeddings, so semantic search may fall back to keyword search
# ALTERNATIVE_AI_API_KEY=sk-...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ALTERNATIVE_AI_API_KEY=sk-...  # For client-side AI features

# Custom AI Endpoints (Optional)
# Override default API endpoints if using self-hosted or alternative services
# OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://api.openai.com/v1
# ALTERNATIVE_AI_ENDPOINT=https://api.example.com/v1

# AI Feature Notes:
# - Both keys are OPTIONAL - AI features gracefully degrade to basic implementations when not configured
# - OpenAI is recommended for best semantic search results (has embeddings API)
# - Server-side keys (without NEXT_PUBLIC_) are more secure but only work for server-side features
# - Client-side keys (NEXT_PUBLIC_*) enable real-time AI features but are exposed to clients
# - Consider implementing rate limiting to control API costs


